    <i class="fa-fw fa fa-exchange"></i>
    <b>Want to buy {{= xcp}}?</b> Beyond using the decentralized exchange in {{= name}}, other options for purchasing {{= xcp}} are
    <a href="{{= xcp_store_url}}" target="_blank">listed here</a>.
</div>
{{ } }}

<div id="gettingStartedNotice" data-bind="fadeVisibleInOnly: WALLET.isNew() && !WALLET.isOldWallet() && window._BALANCES_HAS_LOADED_ALREADY === undefined" class="alert alert-success alert-block">
    <a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#">Ã—</a>
    <h4 class="alert-heading padding-bottom-10">Welcome to {{= name}}!</h4>
    We've created an address for you to get started. You can send and receive both {{= btc_name}} and {{= xcp_name}} tokens with it.
    To start using the wallet, simply send some {{= btc}} or {{= xcp}} to the address (just single click on the address string
    itself to select it, then copy that text, which you can then give to others or use to
    send funds to).
    {{ if (testnet.faucet_url) { }}
    <span data-bind="visible: USE_TESTNET">Note that, on testnet, you can use a
    <b><a href="{{= testnet.faucet_url}}" target="_blank">Testnet faucet</a> to get {{= btc}} to start with</b>.</span>
    {{ } }}
    <br/><br/>
    
    One important thing to know before getting started is that when you perform an action in {{= name}} (i.e. place
    an order, create a token, etc), <b>it doesn't take effect immediately as it must first be confirmed on the {{= btc_name}} blockchain</b>.
    {{= name}} lets you know this by displaying your actions under the <b>Pending Actions</b> panel (the Clock icon on the top bar), and then moving
    them to the <b>Notifications</b> panel (the Checkbox icon) automatically once the network has successfully confirmed them.
    You'll also see the future expected value in parenthesis next to the current balance to better alert you that the change is pending.
    Note that depending on the speed at which blocks are solved, it could take anywhere from 2 to 40 minutes for your actions to be confirmed.<br/><br/>
</div>

<div id="pendingBTCPayNotice" data-bind="fadeVisibleInOnly: needWarningOnExit()" class="alert alert-danger alert-block">
    <i class="fa-fw fa fa-btc"></i>
    <strong>Sell {{= btc}} Pending:</strong> As you have one or more pending or open sell order for {{= btc}}, please stay logged in so that the order(s) can be properly filled.
</div>

